			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Join a team that&#39;s played a huge role in bringing millions of people together since 1998.&nbsp; Evite is looking for an interaction designer that will play a key role in the design and development of Evite&#39;s future web and mobile applications. You&#39;ll be working with fellow interaction designers, product managers, UI designers and web developers to help build &amp; enhance features across Evite&#39;s invitation management platform. You&#39;ll also have an opportunity to continue to evolve and expand the Evite brand by working on new product initiatives such as Evite Postmark (www.postmark.com) and future events based mobile applications.</p>
<p>
Why work here</p>
<ul>
<li>
Work for the largest online invitation company that ranks amongst the top trafficked US websites</li>
<li>
Design in a lean and agile startup like environment</li>
<li>
Take part in the ideation and refinement of broad and conceptual ideas and turn them into simple and elegant user interfaces that are utilized by millions of people</li>
<li>
Play amongst some of the best ping pong and foosball players in the LA tech scene</li>
</ul>
<p>
Requirements</p>
<ul>
<li>
You&#39;re able to create design deliverables such as user flows, wireframes, mockups and presentations that provide annotated design specifications</li>
<li>
You&#39;re familiar with industry standard graphic design tools such as Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, etc...) and have a preferred diagramming tool (Axure RP, Keynote, InDesign, etc..)</li>
<li>
Link to portfolio with samples of recent work is a must</li>
</ul>
<p>
Pluses</p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience designing and developing your own simple website or application</li>
<li>
You exhibit strong visual design skills and have a knack for creating pixel-perfect comps, when necessary</li>
</ul>
